{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-98627ea3f0966503", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# OmniVoice: Towards Omnilingual Zero-Shot Text-to-Speech with Diffusion Language Models\narXiv: 2604.00688\nAuthors: Han Zhu, Lingxuan Ye, Wei Kang, Zengwei Yao, Liyong Guo, Fangjun Kuang, Zhifeng Han, Weiji Zhuang, Long Lin, Daniel Povey\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduction of a single-stage discrete non-autoregressive TTS architecture that directly maps text to multi-codebook acoustic tokens, bypassing the error propagation and information bottlenecks of two-stage pipelines.\n  2. Proposal of a full-codebook random masking strategy that enables dense loss computation across all codebooks to significantly enhance training efficiency and generative quality.\n  3. Demonstration that initializing the bidirectional Transformer backbone with pre-trained autoregressive LLM weights successfully resolves the intelligibility challenge in single-stage discrete NAR TTS models.\n  4. Creation of a 581k-hour multilingual dataset curated from open-source data, enabling the broadest language coverage to date for a zero-shot TTS model with support for over 600 languages.\n  5. Achievement of state-of-the-art performance in intelligibility, speaker similarity, and naturalness across Chinese, English, and diverse massive multilingual benchmarks.\n  6. Integration of multi-dimensional controllability features, including prompt denoising, speaker-attribute-based voice design, and fine-grained paralinguistic and phonetic control.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Transformer, TTS/功能-多语言", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "98a9a38b-97c4-4f62-9652-7dd7b7ca3c40", "uuid": "95b27471-db4a-4ef6-88a4-eeee17054206", "timestamp": "2026-07-24T07:07:57.546Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# OmniVoice: Towards Omnilingual Zero-Shot Text-to-Speech with Diffusion Language Models\narXiv: 2604.00688\nAuthors: Han Zhu, Lingxuan Ye, Wei Kang, Zengwei Yao, Liyong Guo, Fangjun Kuang, Zhifeng Han, Weiji Zhuang, Long Lin, Daniel Povey\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduction of a single-stage discrete non-autoregressive TTS architecture that directly maps text to multi-codebook acoustic tokens, bypassing the error propagation and information bottlenecks of two-stage pipelines.\n  2. Proposal of a full-codebook random masking strategy that enables dense loss computation across all codebooks to significantly enhance training efficiency and generative quality.\n  3. Demonstration that initializing the bidirectional Transformer backbone with pre-trained autoregressive LLM weights successfully resolves the intelligibility challenge in single-stage discrete NAR TTS models.\n  4. Creation of a 581k-hour multilingual dataset curated from open-source data, enabling the broadest language coverage to date for a zero-shot TTS model with support for over 600 languages.\n  5. Achievement of state-of-the-art performance in intelligibility, speaker similarity, and naturalness across Chinese, English, and diverse massive multilingual benchmarks.\n  6. Integration of multi-dimensional controllability features, including prompt denoising, speaker-attribute-based voice design, and fine-grained paralinguistic and phonetic control.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Transformer, TTS/功能-多语言", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
