{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-b4125a7bf3debde9", "type": "tool_result", "content": "Fig. 1. Overview of Faster IndexTTS-2.\n\nIn this paper, we present Faster IndexTTS-2, a fully accelerated\nIndexTTS-2 on GPUs for production deployment using TensorRT\nand TensorRT-LLM. Our main contributions are as follows:\nWe accelerate all neural network components of IndexTTS-2 using\nTensorRT and TensorRT-LLM, achieving up to 3.6× end-to-end\nspeedup and up to 5.0× speedup on the autoregressive GPT.\n• We present a reusable methodology for adapting TensorRT-LLM\nto autoregressive TTS models, providing a practical reference for\naccelerating similar autoregressive speech models on GPUs.\n• We enable streaming synthesis with low Time-To-First-Audio\n(TTFA), crucial for latency-sensitive interactive applications.\n• We enable batched inference across all components to maximize\nGPU utilization, improving synthesis concurrency and throughput.\n• We systematically benchmark both inference efficiency and synthesis quality, providing practical insights for production deployment\nof autoregressive speech models.\n•\n\nII. S YSTEM D ESIGN\nA. Preliminary: IndexTTS-2\nIndexTTS-2 [1] is a cascaded autoregressive zero-shot text-tospeech model consisting of three core modules. The Text-to-Semantic\nmodule is a decoder-only autoregressive GPT [19] that generates\nsemantic codec tokens from text, conditioned on speaker latents and\nemotion embedding extracted from reference audio via Conformerbased [20] perceiver conditioners, along with a speed embedding.\nThe Semantic-to-Mel module employs conditional flow matching [21]\n\n\fTABLE I\nL ATENCY BREAKDOWN , OVERALL PERFORMANCE , AND SYNTHESIS QUALITY OF I NDEX TTS-2 VS . FASTER I NDEX TTS-2 ACROSS PRECISIONS ON THE\nS EED -TTS TEST SETS . A LL LATENCIES IN MILLISECONDS ( MS ). W8A16 AND W4A16 QUANTIZATION ARE APPLIED ONLY TO THE GPT COMPONENT.\nSeed-TTS test-en\n\nSeed-TTS test-zh\n\nIndexTTS-2 (PyTorch)\n\nFaster IndexTTS-2 (TRT/TRT-LLM)\n\nIndexTTS-2 (PyTorch)\n\nFaster IndexTTS-2 (TRT/TRT-LLM)\n\nFP32\n\nFP16\n\nFP32\n\nFP16\n\nW8A16\n\nW4A16\n\nFP32\n\nFP16\n\nFP32\n\nFP16\n\nW8A16\n\nW4A16\n\nLatency\nBreakdown\n\nPreprocessing↓\nGPT↓\nDiT↓\nVocoder↓\n\n115.6\n2539.7\n423.7\n68.0\n\n150.2\n3137.6\n494.1\n94.6\n\n42.4\n676.5\n481.1\n60.3\n\n50.0\n506.6\n281.5\n35.8\n\n49.2\n479.6\n297.4\n35.9\n\n49.8\n476.3\n296.9\n35.0\n\n96.4\n3598.7\n415.8\n74.7\n\n113.7\n4432.7\n483.4\n90.2\n\n29.0\n1004.7\n626.3\n71.5\n\n35.9\n748.7\n375.5\n50.4\n\n36.9\n701.5\n392.8\n50.3\n\n36.7\n736.0\n400.1\n51.2\n\nOverall\n\nLatency↓\nRTF↓\n\n3147.2\n0.84\n\n3876.8\n1.03\n\n1260.8\n0.34\n\n874.5\n0.24\n\n862.7\n0.23\n\n858.5\n0.24\n\n4185.8\n0.76\n\n5120.3\n0.93\n\n1732.1\n0.31\n\n1211.1\n0.22\n\n1182.0\n0.21\n\n1224.6\n0.22\n\nQuality\n\nWER (%)↓\nSIM-o↑\nUTMOS↑\n\n1.84\n0.706\n3.62\n\n1.82\n0.705\n3.60\n\n2.03\n0.703\n3.61\n\n1.97\n0.698\n3.53\n\n2.01\n0.699\n3.53", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "98a9a38b-97c4-4f62-9652-7dd7b7ca3c40", "uuid": "272f7874-11db-46b2-9991-688728977cc1", "timestamp": "2026-07-24T07:09:18.080Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "Fig. 1. Overview of Faster IndexTTS-2.\n\nIn this paper, we present Faster IndexTTS-2, a fully accelerated\nIndexTTS-2 on GPUs for production deployment using TensorRT\nand TensorRT-LLM. Our main contributions are as follows:\nWe accelerate all neural network components of IndexTTS-2 using\nTensorRT and TensorRT-LLM, achieving up to 3.6× end-to-end\nspeedup and up to 5.0× speedup on the autoregressive GPT.\n• We present a reusable methodology for adapting TensorRT-LLM\nto autoregressive TTS models, providing a practical reference for\naccelerating similar autoregressive speech models on GPUs.\n• We enable streaming synthesis with low Time-To-First-Audio\n(TTFA), crucial for latency-sensitive interactive applications.\n• We enable batched inference across all components to maximize\nGPU utilization, improving synthesis concurrency and throughput.\n• We systematically benchmark both inference efficiency and synthesis quality, providing practical insights for production deployment\nof autoregressive speech models.\n•\n\nII. S YSTEM D ESIGN\nA. Preliminary: IndexTTS-2\nIndexTTS-2 [1] is a cascaded autoregressive zero-shot text-tospeech model consisting of three core modules. The Text-to-Semantic\nmodule is a decoder-only autoregressive GPT [19] that generates\nsemantic codec tokens from text, conditioned on speaker latents and\nemotion embedding extracted from reference audio via Conformerbased [20] perceiver conditioners, along with a speed embedding.\nThe Semantic-to-Mel module employs conditional flow matching [21]\n\n\fTABLE I\nL ATENCY BREAKDOWN , OVERALL PERFORMANCE , AND SYNTHESIS QUALITY OF I NDEX TTS-2 VS . FASTER I NDEX TTS-2 ACROSS PRECISIONS ON THE\nS EED -TTS TEST SETS . A LL LATENCIES IN MILLISECONDS ( MS ). W8A16 AND W4A16 QUANTIZATION ARE APPLIED ONLY TO THE GPT COMPONENT.\nSeed-TTS test-en\n\nSeed-TTS test-zh\n\nIndexTTS-2 (PyTorch)\n\nFaster IndexTTS-2 (TRT/TRT-LLM)\n\nIndexTTS-2 (PyTorch)\n\nFaster IndexTTS-2 (TRT/TRT-LLM)\n\nFP32\n\nFP16\n\nFP32\n\nFP16\n\nW8A16\n\nW4A16\n\nFP32\n\nFP16\n\nFP32\n\nFP16\n\nW8A16\n\nW4A16\n\nLatency\nBreakdown\n\nPreprocessing↓\nGPT↓\nDiT↓\nVocoder↓\n\n115.6\n2539.7\n423.7\n68.0\n\n150.2\n3137.6\n494.1\n94.6\n\n42.4\n676.5\n481.1\n60.3\n\n50.0\n506.6\n281.5\n35.8\n\n49.2\n479.6\n297.4\n35.9\n\n49.8\n476.3\n296.9\n35.0\n\n96.4\n3598.7\n415.8\n74.7\n\n113.7\n4432.7\n483.4\n90.2\n\n29.0\n1004.7\n626.3\n71.5\n\n35.9\n748.7\n375.5\n50.4\n\n36.9\n701.5\n392.8\n50.3\n\n36.7\n736.0\n400.1\n51.2\n\nOverall\n\nLatency↓\nRTF↓\n\n3147.2\n0.84\n\n3876.8\n1.03\n\n1260.8\n0.34\n\n874.5\n0.24\n\n862.7\n0.23\n\n858.5\n0.24\n\n4185.8\n0.76\n\n5120.3\n0.93\n\n1732.1\n0.31\n\n1211.1\n0.22\n\n1182.0\n0.21\n\n1224.6\n0.22\n\nQuality\n\nWER (%)↓\nSIM-o↑\nUTMOS↑\n\n1.84\n0.706\n3.62\n\n1.82\n0.705\n3.60\n\n2.03\n0.703\