{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-87c756f6baddd970", "type": "tool_result", "content": "2407.05407\n===\n# CosyVoice: A Scalable Multilingual Zero-shot Text-to-speech Synthesizer based on Supervised Semantic Tokens\narXiv: 2407.05407\nAuthors: Zhihao Du, Qian Chen, Shiliang Zhang, Kai Hu, Heng Lu, Yexin Yang, Hangrui Hu, Siqi Zheng, Yue Gu, Ziyang Ma, Zhifu Gao, Zhijie Yan\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We are the first to integrate supervised speech tokens into text-to-speech models, enhancing content consistency and speaker similarity in zero-shot voice cloning.\n  2. We propose CosyVoice, a scalable zero-shot TTS synthesis system that combines an LLM for text-to-token generation with a conditional flow matching model for token-to-speech synthesis, forsaking the need for additional phonemizers and forced aligners.\n  3. We refine the quality of generated speech by incorporating the x-vector into the LLM to separate speech modeling into semantic, speaker, and prosody components, and optimize the flow matching process with classifier-free guidance, a cosine scheduler, and masked conditions.\n\nTags: TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/功能-多说话人, 压缩/监督-有监督, 压缩/语义声学-语义", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "98a9a38b-97c4-4f62-9652-7dd7b7ca3c40", "uuid": "f6f3c851-92f6-4cf4-829a-a9a277014c88", "timestamp": "2026-07-24T07:10:19.489Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "2407.05407\n===\n# CosyVoice: A Scalable Multilingual Zero-shot Text-to-speech Synthesizer based on Supervised Semantic Tokens\narXiv: 2407.05407\nAuthors: Zhihao Du, Qian Chen, Shiliang Zhang, Kai Hu, Heng Lu, Yexin Yang, Hangrui Hu, Siqi Zheng, Yue Gu, Ziyang Ma, Zhifu Gao, Zhijie Yan\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We are the first to integrate supervised speech tokens into text-to-speech models, enhancing content consistency and speaker similarity in zero-shot voice cloning.\n  2. We propose CosyVoice, a scalable zero-shot TTS synthesis system that combines an LLM for text-to-token generation with a conditional flow matching model for token-to-speech synthesis, forsaking the need for additional phonemizers and forced aligners.\n  3. We refine the quality of generated speech by incorporating the x-vector into the LLM to separate speech modeling into semantic, speaker, and prosody components, and optimize the flow matching process with classifier-free guidance, a cosine scheduler, and masked conditions.\n\nTags: TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/功能-多说话人, 压缩/监督-有监督, 压缩/语义声学-语义", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-b07ff4c133e69607", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# CosyVoice 2: Scalable Streaming Speech Synthesis with Large Language Models\narXiv: 2412.10117\nAuthors: Zhihao Du, Yuxuan Wang, Qian Chen, Xian Shi, Xiang Lv, Tianyu Zhao, Zhifu Gao, Yexin Yang, Changfeng Gao, Hui Wang, Fan Yu, Huadai Liu, Zhengyan Sheng, Yue Gu, Chong Deng, Wen Wang, Shiliang Zhang, Zhijie Yan, Jingren Zhou\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introducing CosyVoice 2, a scalable streaming speech synthesis model that integrates large language models with a speech decoder.\n  2. Designing a unified architecture that seamlessly supports both streaming and non-streaming speech synthesis.\n  3. Developing a large language model equipped with block-wise causal attention to effectively balance lookahead context and streaming latency.\n  4. Implementing a modified finite scalar quantization strategy with an adaptive weight to achieve high-compression and high-accuracy speech tokenization.\n  5. Demonstrating through comprehensive experiments that the proposed model significantly outperforms its predecessor and achieves state-of-the-art performance in speech synthesis.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/功能-流式, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/控制-参考语音\n===\n# Spark-TTS: An Efficient LLM-Based Text-to-Speech Model with Single-Stream Decoupled Speech Tokens\narXiv: 2503.01710\nAuthors: Xinsheng Wang, Mingqi Jiang, Ziyang Ma, Ziyu Zhang, Songxiang Liu, Linqin Li, Zheng Liang, Qixi Zheng, Rui Wang, Xiaoqin Feng, Weizhen Bian, Zhen Ye, Sitong Cheng, Ruibin Yuan, Zhixian Zhao, Xinfa Zhu, Jiahao Pan, Liumeng Xue, Pengcheng Zhu, Yunlin Chen, Zhifei Li, Xie Chen, Lei Xie, Yike Guo, Wei Xue\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present BiCodec, a unified speech tokenization that generates a hybrid token stream combining semantic and global tokens to maintain linguistic fidelity while enabling attribute control.\n  2. Spark-TTS implements a comprehensive attribute control system that seamlessly integrates both coarse-grained and fine-grained voice parameters within a text LLM-compatible architecture.\n  3. We introduce VoxBox, a rigorously curated 100,000-hour speech corpus with comprehensive attribute annotations to establish a standardized benchmark for TTS research.\n\nTags: TTS, 压缩, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, 压缩/量化-VQ, 压缩/量化-FSQ, 压缩/语义声学-语义, TTS/控制-参考语音", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "98a9a38b-97c4-4f62-9652-7dd7b7ca3c40", "uuid": "a2c12b48-03e6-40fa-9811-300b0d3fb3d3", "timestamp": "2026-07-24T07:10:19.955Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# CosyVoice 2: Scalable Streaming Speech Synthesis with Large Language Models\narXiv: 2412.10117\nAuthors: Zhihao Du, Yuxuan Wang, Qian Chen, Xian Shi, Xiang Lv, Tianyu Zhao, Zhifu Gao, Yexin Yang, Changfeng Gao, Hui Wang, Fan Yu, Huadai Liu, Zhengyan Sheng, Yue Gu, Chong Deng, Wen Wang, Shiliang Zhang, Zhijie Yan, Jingren Zhou\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introducing CosyVoice 2, a scalable streaming speech synthesis model that integrates large language models with a speech decoder.\n  2. Designing a unified architecture that seamlessly supports both streaming and non-streaming speech synthesis.\n  3. Developing a large language model equipped with block-wise causal attention to effectively balance lookahead context and streaming latency.\n  4. Implementing a modified finite scalar quantization strategy with an adaptive weight to achieve high-compression and high-accuracy speech tokenization.\n  5. Demonstrating through comprehensive experiments that the proposed model significantly outperforms its predecessor and achieves state-of-the-art performance in speech synthesis.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/功能-流式, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/控制-参考语音\n===\n# Spark-TTS: An Efficient LLM-Based Text-to-Speech Model with Single-Stream Decoupled Speech Tokens\narXiv: 2503.01710\nAuthors: Xinsheng Wang, Mingqi Jiang, Ziyang Ma, Ziyu Zhang, Songxiang Liu, Linqin Li, Zheng Liang, Qixi Zheng, Rui Wang, Xiaoqin Feng, Weizhen Bian, Zhen Ye, Sitong Cheng, Ruibin Yuan, Zhixian Zhao, Xinfa Zhu, Jiahao Pan, Liumeng Xue, Pengcheng Zhu, Yunlin Chen, Zhifei Li, Xie Chen, Lei Xie, Yike Guo, Wei Xue\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present BiCodec, a unified speech tokenization that generates a hybrid token stream combining semantic and global tokens to maintain linguistic fidelity while enabling attribute control.\n  2. Spark-TTS implements a comprehensive attribute control system that seamlessly integrates both coarse-grained and fine-grained voice parameters within a text LLM-compatible architecture.\n  3. We introduce VoxBox, a rigorously curated 100,000-hour speech corpus with comprehensive attribute annotations to establish a standardized benchmark for TTS research.\n\nTags: TTS, 压缩, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, 压缩/量化-VQ, 压缩/量化-FSQ, 压缩/语义声学-语义, TTS/控制-参考语音", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
