{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-96ec40e8535b442a", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# IndexTTS 2.5 Technical Report\narXiv: 2601.03888\nAuthors: Yunpei Li, Xun Zhou, Jinchao Wang, Lu Wang, Yong Wu, Siyi Zhou, Yiquan Zhou, Jingchen Shu\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Semantic codec frame rate is reduced from 50 Hz to 25 Hz to halve sequence length and lower training and inference costs.\n  2. The U-DiT backbone in the Semantic-to-Mel module is replaced with a more efficient Zipformer architecture to reduce parameters and accelerate mel-spectrogram generation.\n  3. Three explicit cross-lingual modeling strategies are proposed to enable robust zero-shot multilingual emotional TTS and cross-lingual emotion transfer across Chinese, English, Japanese, and Spanish.\n  4. Group Relative Policy Optimization is applied to post-train the Text-to-Semantic module, improving pronunciation accuracy and prosodic naturalness.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/功能-RL优化", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "98a9a38b-97c4-4f62-9652-7dd7b7ca3c40", "uuid": "3b20a4bf-18c8-4f94-a6f5-74394a1d8644", "timestamp": "2026-07-24T07:10:43.924Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# IndexTTS 2.5 Technical Report\narXiv: 2601.03888\nAuthors: Yunpei Li, Xun Zhou, Jinchao Wang, Lu Wang, Yong Wu, Siyi Zhou, Yiquan Zhou, Jingchen Shu\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Semantic codec frame rate is reduced from 50 Hz to 25 Hz to halve sequence length and lower training and inference costs.\n  2. The U-DiT backbone in the Semantic-to-Mel module is replaced with a more efficient Zipformer architecture to reduce parameters and accelerate mel-spectrogram generation.\n  3. Three explicit cross-lingual modeling strategies are proposed to enable robust zero-shot multilingual emotional TTS and cross-lingual emotion transfer across Chinese, English, Japanese, and Spanish.\n  4. Group Relative Policy Optimization is applied to post-train the Text-to-Semantic module, improving pronunciation accuracy and prosodic naturalness.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/功能-RL优化", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
